# Privacy Policy

## Introduction
At Kreacon, operated by Beacon, we value your privacy and are committed to protecting your personal data. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your data when you use our platform, and outlines your rights regarding your data.

By using Kreacon, you agree to the terms outlined in this Privacy Policy. Please read it carefully.

## 1. Data Collection

### Personal Information
We collect the following personal information when you register or use our platform:
- **Email address**
- **Username**
- **Password**
- **Profile image** (optional)
- **User-generated content** (e.g., digital artwork submissions)
- **IP address** and device information for security purposes.

### Age Verification and Parental Consent
If you are under the age of 16, you must obtain **parental consent** before using our platform. We will not collect personal data from users under 16 unless we have verifiable parental consent.

- **Age Verification**: During registration, we will ask for your age.
- **Parental Consent**: If you are under 16, we will ask for your parent or guardian's email address to obtain consent. You will not be able to complete registration until parental consent is verified.

## 2. Data Usage
We use the data we collect for the following purposes:
- To enable you to participate in the platform's features (e.g., submit artwork, compete in events).
- To provide customer support and respond to your inquiries.
- To improve the platform’s functionality and user experience.
- To ensure the security of our platform and prevent fraudulent activity.
- To comply with legal obligations.

## 3. Data Retention
We retain your personal data as long as your account is active or as needed to provide services. If you wish to delete your account, you can do so at any time by contacting us. Your data will be deleted within a reasonable time after account deletion.

## 4. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We will never sell your personal information to third parties. However, we may share your data with:
- **Service providers** who help us maintain the platform, such as cloud storage providers or payment processors.
- **Legal authorities** if required by law to comply with a subpoena, legal process, or similar request.

## 5. Security
We take reasonable measures to protect your personal data. However, no data transmission over the internet is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee the absolute security of your data.

## 6. Your Rights
As a user, you have the following rights regarding your personal data:
- **Access**: You can request a copy of the personal data we hold about you.
- **Correction**: You can request that we correct any incorrect or incomplete data.
- **Deletion**: You can request that we delete your personal data, subject to certain conditions.
- **Objection**: You can object to certain types of processing, including direct marketing.
- **Withdraw Consent**: You can withdraw any consent you have given for data processing at any time.

To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at [Contact Information].

## 7. International Data Transfers
Kreacon is hosted in the European Union, and we comply with applicable data protection regulations when transferring data.

## 8. Changes to the Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated revision date. Please review this Privacy Policy periodically.

## 9. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, please contact us at [Email Address] or [Postal Address].

